Package: Tivy
Type: Package
Title: Tools for Fisheries Data Analysis and Visualization
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Hans Ttito
Maintainer: Hans Ttito <kvttitos@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Description: Provides functions for loading, processing, and analyzing fisheries data,
    including information from fishing logbooks, size measurements, and fishing grounds 
    from Peru's Ministry of Production, as well as notifications issued for preventive
    closures. The package includes tools for geographical visualization of fishing areas,
    statistical modeling of fish populations, and processing of regulatory documents.
    Contains built-in datasets for Peruvian coastal coordinates and parallel lines at
    different nautical mile distances from shore, which are useful for analyzing fishing
    activities within restricted zones.
Imports:
  dplyr,
  tidyr,
  lubridate,
  stringi,
  pdftools,
  stringr,
  future,
  future.apply,
  leaflet,
  ggplot2,
  RColorBrewer,
  patchwork,
  rnaturalearth,
  scales
